The chat overlay has dark theme by default in index.css:322:


.co-wrapper { @apply bg-slate-900 border-slate-800; }
And inside that wrapper, the message bubble container has a dark background. The FormRenderer's suggestion dropdowns use absolute positioning, but the parent elements chain dark colors (bg-slate-900 on .co-wrapper, bg-slate-900 on body defaults, text-slate-100 / text-slate-200 globally). Even though you set bg-white and inline backgroundColor: '#ffffff', there are likely CSS specificity wars — the Tailwind classes on li items (like hover:bg-blue-50) or inherited text-* colors from parent dark-theme classes are overriding or making the white background invisible against a white page, or the dark text on dark background making it unreadable.

The real problem: the dropdowns render inside the .co-wrapper → dark slate-900 DOM tree. Tailwind's dark-mode classes and the parent's inherited text colors are bleeding through.

