4. ROOT CAUSE DIAGNOSIS
The dropdown <ul> is rendered as a child of the form field which is inside <div class="... co-wrapper">. The .co-wrapper has @apply bg-slate-900 (line 322 of index.css). While the FormRenderer's wrapper has bg-white, the Tailwind hover:bg-blue-50 class on li elements and inherited text-* from the dark parent chain is the problem. The inline style on the <ul> background should work, but the className text colors on li like text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 for items and text-[10px] text-slate-400 for descriptions are Tailwind classes that may get overridden or not render visibly.

The most reliable fix: portal the dropdowns out of the DOM tree entirely (use React portals or a simple absolute positioning on body), or — simpler — use style properties for everything on the dropdown with !important equivalent.

5. WHAT I RECOMMEND
The cleanest fix: add style properties for both background AND color on every element inside the dropdown (ul, li, child divs), plus use a higher z-index and position: fixed from body, OR just move the suggestion lists to render at the root level with refs. But the quickest reliable fix:


- ul: inline style background=#ffffff
- each li: inline style color=#0f172a  
- inner divs: inline style color=#0f172a and #64748b
- remove ALL className text-color classes from dropdown content
- use style for background on li hover via CSS variable or inline on each
